definition: many/much/often/a lot of/numerous/more/in excess/how (to what extent)/multi-/Taiwan pr. [duo2] when it means "how"
many/much/often/a lot of/numerous/more/in excess/how (to what extent)/multi-/Taiwan pr. [duo2] when it means "how"

sentences.english: The sacred place of the revolution invites a good many visitors.
sentences.chinese: 革命圣地吸引着许许多多的参观者。

sentences.english: Friends like capital, the more friends are the better the entrepreneur is.
sentences.chinese: 朋友尤如资本金，对创业者来说是多多益善。

sentences.english: Take a candid shot of WeiSheng shitting and he will give you the smell of a lifetime.
sentences.chinese: 偷拍多多大便，他会放一生难忘的臭屁给你闻。

sentences.english: I was always able to figure out more or less where he was.
sentences.chinese: 我总能多多少少地找到他在哪里。

sentences.english: She can more or less assume his cocksureness.
sentences.chinese: 母鸡可以多多少少地装出公鸡的自信。

sentences.english: After Marquis also invited a lot of attention.
sentences.chinese: 以后还请侯爵多多关照。

sentences.english: Practice Sideslipping and take full advantage of your edge.
sentences.chinese: 多多练习侧滑并且充分利用你的板刃。

sentences.english: These are walls much, much larger than the ones that surround my cell.
sentences.chinese: 这是比围在我牢房四周的墙壁还要厚得多多的墙壁。

sentences.english: It takes time and many revisions to get it right.
sentences.chinese: 要想把它做好得花时间，还要多多修改才成。

sentences.english: Money mother hope xu fei don't bother to mention.
sentences.chinese: 钱母希望许飞不要再来打搅多多。

sentences.english: Besides, they also seek out English corners and practice their English a lot.
sentences.chinese: 而且他们都设法找到英语角去多多地练习讲英语。

sentences.english: The many flags lend colur to the streets.
sentences.chinese: 这许许多多旗帜给街道增添了色彩。

sentences.english: He is always enthusiastic about life and eager to participate in all activies.
sentences.chinese: 他一直很热情，很想在课堂上多多练习。

sentences.english: I'd finger paint more, and point the fingers less.
sentences.chinese: 我要少对他指手划脚，却多多抓着他的小手一起画画。

sentences.english: A profusion of leaves bursts out on trees in the springtime.
sentences.chinese: 春天许许多多的叶子从树上冒出来。

sentences.english: Again, more or less a sub-category of "appeal" and "overlapping action".
sentences.chinese: 这个，多多少少是吸引力和交迭动作的子原理。
